# Docker build context is the repo root (docker-compose sets context: .), so THIS
# file — at the context root — is the one Docker actually reads. A .dockerignore
# living inside apps/web/ is ignored by the build. Without these excludes a stale
# apps/web/.next leaks into the image via `COPY apps/web/ ./`, and `next build`
# then compiles incrementally on top of old output and serves stale chunks.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/.turbo

# Never bake secrets or local env into an image (keep examples).
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Local dev database + logs + OS cruft.
apps/api/prisma/*.db
apps/api/prisma/*.db-journal
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store

# VCS / CI metadata isn't needed in the build.
.git
.github
